<p>The late, full moon cast tiny glimmers of light on the huddled forms around the room. One of Running Dog&rsquo;s men snored deeply on the stairs. Elmer coughed, moaned, and sighed in his sleep.</p>

<p>&ldquo;What a fuckin&rsquo; zoo, man,&rdquo; Running Dog said sleepily. My nipple slid half out of his mouth. He caught it in his teeth, sucked painfully hard, then laughed at the smacking sound. I watched the moon. She was my witness.</p>

